To suppress serializing properties with null values using Jackson &gt;2.0, you can [configure the `ObjectMapper` directly][1], or make use of the [`@JsonInclude`][2] annotation:

    mapper.setSerializationInclusion(Include.NON_NULL);

or:

    @JsonInclude(Include.NON_NULL)
    class Foo
    {
      String bar;
    }

Alternatively, you could use `@JsonInclude` in a getter so that the attribute would be shown if the value is not null.

A more complete example is available in [my answer][3] to https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11449211/.


